<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97628405329974></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97628405329974><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97628405329974>RE: Magician or wizard??????</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97628405329974#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 8th 2:01 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wizards are mostly torture to play until you get to lvl 20.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then they suddenly become fun.  The reason is that we are sitting ducks and are not better than a mage until that point.  Then suddenly we get our teleport spells and the real fun begins.  A wizard does not have pets until lvl 55 or so and that is our weakness.  But we have an endless supply of money coming to us because we become the taxi cabs of the game.  I have seen people pay 50pp for a simple teleport before.  Another way is to find yourself an enchanter friend that is a jeweler and become their salesman... a wizard can teleport all over and sell stuff and get a nice cut of the profits too.  I was able to sell stuff for a friend of mine and made 875pp in less than 30 min.  That is NOT a bad deal no matter what lvl you are and I was only lvl 24 at the time.  Another thing is that we are the ONLY class that can teleport you to other planes when you get to high levels.  So it is as simple as this... Do you want to be useful at most all lvls (A mage), or SUPER USEFUL after lvl 20? (A wizard).... I prefer the wizard because of the money and the teleports.  It is worth it.<br><br>Sincerely,<br>Alexandri Tigress (Erollsi Marr Server)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
